  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Aim is to evaluate outcomes of inguinal hernia repair incorporating the standard Lichtenstein
      (open) repair using Biodesign IHM in a double blind (physician evaluator and patient will be
      blinded), randomized, prospective comparative study with polypropylene mesh. Primary outcome
      is recurrence at 1 year. Hernia recurrence will be confirmed via ultrasound or CT scan.
    </textblock>
